{{Infobox company | name = Broad Green Pictures LLC. | logo = Broad Green Pictures logo.svg | logo_padding = 15px | caption = | founder = {{Plainlist| *Daniel Hammond *Gabriel Hammond}} | foundation = 2014; 3 years ago | location_city = [[Los Angeles]], [[California]] | location_country = [[United States]] | key_people = | industry = [[Motion picture]] | products = {{Plainlist| *[[Film distribution]] *[[Film production]]}} | type = Private | subsid = [[Mister Smith Entertainment]] (45%)<ref name="auto">{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2015/02/broad-green-pictures-david-garrett-mister-smith-entertainment-1201381178/|title=Broad Green Pictures Acquires 45% Stake In David Garrett’s Mister Smith Entertainment|first=Ali|last=Jaafar|date=25 February 2015|publisher=|accessdate=2 August 2017}}</ref> | homepage = {{URL|http://www.broadgreen.com}} }} '''Broad Green Pictures''' is an American film production and financing company. It was founded in 2014 by CEO [[Gabriel Hammond]] and Chief Creative Officer, Daniel Hammond.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://broadgreen.com/#about-us|title=Broad Green Pictures - New Movies & Future Releases|website=Broad Green Pictures|accessdate=2 August 2017}}</ref> On August 2, 2017, the company shut down its entire production division after a string of [[Box office bomb|box office disappointments]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2017/film/news/broad-green-cuts-1202513596/|title=Broad Green Kills Production Division, Lays Off 15 Employees After String of Flops|first=Brent|last=Lang|date=2 August 2017|publisher=|accessdate=2 August 2017}}</ref>
== Management == On February 25, 2015, Broad Green Pictures acquired a 45% stake in David Garrett’s London-based sales and distribution outfit, [[Mister Smith Entertainment]].<ref name="auto"/> Adam Keen, former VP of [[Warner Bros.]] was hired on March 25, 2015 to take the job as head of publicity.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Lang|first1=Brent|title=Adam Keen Leaves Warner Bros. to Run Publicity at Broad Green|url=https://variety.com/2015/film/news/adam-keen-leaves-warner-bros-to-run-publicity-at-broad-green-1201459091/|accessdate=April 9, 2015|date=March 25, 2015}}</ref> In April 2015, Christopher Tricario was hired as EVP of business affairs and general counsel.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2015/04/christopher-tricarico-joins-broad-green-pictures-1201414131/|title=Broad Green Pictures Hires Christopher Tricarico As EVP Biz Affairs|website=Deadline Hollywood|first=Kinsley|last=Lowe|date=April 21, 2015|accessdate=February 17, 2016}}</ref> That same month Jeremy Fuchs as the technology officer.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2015/04/broad-green-sets-jeremy-fuchs-as-tech-chief-1201419031/|title=Broad Green Sets Jeremy Fuchs As Tech Chief|website=Deadline Hollywood|first=Erik|last=Pendersen|date=April 30, 2015|accessdate=February 17, 2016}}</ref> In May 2015, Travis Reid was named the president of theatrical distribution.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2015/05/travis-reid-president-of-distribution-broad-green-pictures-1201429692/|title=Travis Reid Named President Of Distribution At Broad Green Pictures|website=Deadline Hollywood|first=Anita|last=Busch|date=May 19, 2015|accessdate=February 17, 2016}}</ref> That same month, Dylan Wiley was hired as the president of specialty releasing.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2015/05/broad-green-dylan-wiley-president-specialty-releasing-1201422150/|title=Broad Green Hires Dylan Wiley To Run Specialty Releasing|website=Deadline Hollywood|first=Patrick|last=Hipes|date=May 7, 2015|accessdate=February 17, 2016}}</ref> In July 2015, Marc Danon joined the company as the president of acquisitions and co-productions, leaving his job as acquisitions and business development senior VP for [[Lionsgate]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2015/07/marc-danon-leaves-lionsgate-for-president-post-at-broad-green-pictures-1201472843/|title=Marc Danon Leaves Lionsgate For President Post At Broad Green Pictures|website=Deadline Hollywood|first=Anita|last=Busch|date=July 9, 2015|accessdate=February 17, 2016}}</ref> On September 3, 2015, Alix Madigan was hired as head of creative affairs, she left Anonymous Content's executive and a staff producer job.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Jaafar|first1=Ali|title=Alix Madigan Joins Broad Green Pictures From Anonymous Content|url=http://deadline.com/2015/09/alix-madigan-broad-green-pictures-anonymous-content-1201513978/|accessdate=September 4, 2015|website=Deadline Hollywood|date=September 3, 2015}}</ref> She has since left the company, and Broad Green Pictures hired Matt Alvarez as President of Production.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://variety.com/2016/film/news/alix-madigan-broad-green-1201787101/|title=Alix Madigan Departs Broad Green as Head of Creative Affairs|last=McNary|first=Dave|date=2016-06-01|newspaper=Variety|language=en-US|access-date=2016-11-15}}</ref> Matt Alvarez is a producer of ''[[Straight Outta Compton (film)|Straight Outta Compton]]'', ''[[Ride Along (film)|Ride Along]]'', and ''[[Ride Along 2]]''.
In September 2016, Richard Fay was announced to be the head of distribution, replacing Travis Reid who previously resigned.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2016/09/broad-green-taps-richie-fay-distribution-head-1201819512/|title=Broad Green Taps Lionsgate’s Richard Fay As President Of Distribution In Wake Of Travis Reid Departure|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|first=Anthony|last=D'Alessandro|date=September 14, 2016|accessdate=September 18, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2016/08/broad-greens-distribution-travis-reid-resigns-1201811922/|title=Broad Green’s Head Of Distribution Travis Reid Resigns|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|first=Anthony|last=D'Alessandro|date=August 31, 2016|accessdate=September 18, 2016}}</ref>
