{{Infobox person
| name = Fantasio
| birth_name = Ricardo Roucau
| birth_date = {{Birth date|1936|10|03}}
| birth_place = [[Buenos Aires, Argentina]]<ref name="Linking Ring Feature">{{Cite magazine|last=|first=|date=June 1996|editor-last=Willmarth|editor-first=Phil|title=Fantasio: Master Magician and Inventor|url=http://askalexander.org/display/40690/Linking+Ring/55|journal=[[The Linking Ring]]|volume=76|issue=6|pages=55–57|subscription=yes|via=}}</ref>
| death_date = {{Death date and age|2017|10|30|1936|10|03}}
}}
'''Ricardo Roucau''' (3 October 1936 – 30 October 2017) was a magician commonly known as '''Fantasio'''.<ref name="Genii In Memoriam">{{Cite magazine|last=Ibañez|first=Maria|date=December 2017|editor-last=Kaufman|editor-first=Richard|title=In Memoriam Fantasio|url=http://geniimagazine.dc.newsmemory.com/?selDate=20171201|journal=[[Genii (magazine)|Genii]]|volume=80|issue=12|pages=11|subscription=yes|via=}}</ref> Roucau previously performed as Ricardo and then as Larry, before being warned in 1961 by [[John Scarne]] that the name would not work for a magician trying to make it in America.<ref name="Genii In Memoriam" /> He also performed with his wife as 'Larry and Daisy'.<ref name="Linking Ring Feature" /> Roucau adopted the name Fantasio after noticing it on a box of [[playing card]]s.<ref name="Genii In Memoriam" /> Roucau was a prolific inventor,<ref name="Linking Ring Feature" /> and [[Mike Caveney]] believes that Fantasio's appearing and disappearing props were at one point the most popular magic props in the world.<ref>{{Cite magazine|last=Caveney|first=Mike|date=September 2014|editor-last=Allen|editor-first=Stan|title=Classic Correspondence from Egyptian Hall Museum|url=https://askalexander.org/display/70038/MAGIC+magazine/15|journal=[[Magic (magazine)|MAGIC]]|volume=24|issue=1|pages=15|subscription=yes|via=}}</ref>

Fantasio was a lifetime member of [[International Brotherhood of Magicians|Ring 45]] and [[Society of American Magicians|Assembly 280]]. In 2010, he was named Dean of Assembly 280.<ref>{{Cite magazine|last=DelVecchio|first=Rick|date=May 2010|title=Ring 45 (Miami, Florida) 2010 Installation and Awards Banquet|url=http://askalexander.org/display/40938/Linking+Ring/33|journal=[[The Linking Ring]]|volume=90|issue=5|pages=32–33|subscription=yes|via=}}</ref>

== Published books ==
* ''Magic with Canes and Candles'' (1970)
* ''My Canes and Candles'' (1990)

