{{refimprove|date=February 2015}} {{Infobox television |image = |genre = |runtime = |creator = Davin Lengyel, Geoff Lapaire |opentheme = |endtheme = |composer = |country = [[Canada]] |network = |picture_format = |company = Space Mop |distributor = |executive_producer = |first_aired = 2012 |last_aired = 2015 |num_seasons = 3 |num_episodes = 24 |list_episodes = |related = }} '''Space Janitors''' was a Canadian [[web series]]. The show focused on two janitors, Darby & Mike, on a space station.
==Characters== The show centers around Social Group 417: * Darby Richards ([[Brendan Halloran]]), a human custodian * Mike Chet ([[Pat Thornton]]), a human custodian * LN6-K aka Elle ([[Tess Degenstein]]), engineer second class * Edith Kingpin ([[Evany Rosen]]), computer psychologist first class * Dennis 4862 ([[Scott Yamamura]]), human clone squall trooper
==Production== The series was created by Davin Lengyel and Geoff Lapaire, digital media producers who were previously associated with the web and television series ''[[Pure Pwnage]]''.<ref>[http://www.omdc.on.ca/WGIGO/Success_Stories/Interactive_Success_Stories/OMDC_SUCCESS_STORY__SPACE_MOP.htm?PageMode=Print "OMDC Success Story: Space Mop"]. Ontario Media Development Corporation.</ref> It premiered in 2012.
Season 3 was partially funded as a [[Kickstarter]] project.<ref>[https://www.theglobeandmail.com/report-on-business/small-business/sb-money/business-funding/top-january-crowdfunders/article16705897/ "Hand-crafted bags, 3-D printers and Space Janitors top crowdfunding list"]. ''[[The Globe and Mail]]'', February 6, 2014.</ref><ref>https://www.kickstarter.com/projects/635272374/space-janitors-webseries-season-3</ref> The third season also received a theatrical screening at Toronto's Royal Cinema on January 9, 2015.<ref>[http://www.space.ca/article/Toronto-Go-see-e28098Space-Janitorse28099-on-the-big-screen-alongside-cast-and-crew "Toronto: Go See Space Janitors on the Big Screen"]. [[Space (Canadian TV channel)|Space]], January 9, 2015.</ref>
==Awards== The series won a [[Canadian Screen Award]] for Digital Media Original Program or Series, Fiction at the [[2nd Canadian Screen Awards]] in 2014.<ref>[https://www.theglobeandmail.com/arts/awards-and-festivals/film-awards/gabrielle-enemy-among-big-winners-at-canadian-screen-awards/article17391201/ "Gabrielle, Enemy among big winners at Canadian Screen Awards"]. ''[[The Globe and Mail]]'', March 9, 2014.</ref> It was also a nominee in the same category at the [[1st Canadian Screen Awards]] in 2013.<ref>[http://www.blogto.com/film/2013/02/the_top_10_toronto_web_series/ "The top 10 Toronto web series"]. ''BlogTO'', February 13, 2013.</ref>
